                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the Book of Books it lies before her “A<lb/> Husband to the Widow, A Father to\n                the<lb/> Fatherless.” This gracious promise, the<lb/> sacred injunction defraud not\n                nor<lb/> oppress them; yes thus she finds her<lb/> bitter grief allayed, the\n                children whom<lb/> God himself makes object of especial<lb/> love, shall she not\n                strive to lead them<lb/> to Him, shall she not seek with earnest<lb/> prayer and\n                trusting hope His guidance<lb/> in that holiest task a mothers training<lb/> of her\n                offspring, and in grateful reliance<lb/> say He who has stricken can console.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">To the <addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee></p>\n            <p>That in our small community, three<lb/> bereavements of the kind alluded to has<lb/>\n                occurred in that many weeks, led to to the<lb/> train of thought that if you\n                    <add>?</add> please dear<lb/> sir you will give place to in the Occident<lb/> I\n                am aware that its adaptation is its only<lb/> merit therefore shall not doubt\n                your<lb/> judgment a kindness if you decline it<lb/> Hoping soon to see you in\n                health and happiness<lb/> and with regard your friend <persName role=\"author\">L B\n                    Hart</persName></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3gt5fz0f/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
